oeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"5e9eeecbd54ebf03cec9d8dec2d550855d529f639d9e66bd5ffe459c404f5049","event_uuid":"aabe5970-5d27-4c57-9c5f-02cdc618cb75","position":{"commit_sha":"aa04cf948a56b771f334896217d298411429beaf","position":"1784455442134804001-aabe5970-5d27-4c57-9c5f-02cdc618cb75"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"412438893fa10177a16ab2a6213f5c06dcd5d90086d029ec88c8f84d1906f0e3","event_uuid":"297911ff-5395-4fe3-b0d5-1d61294ae2ae","position":{"commit_sha":"aa04cf948a56b771f334896217d298411429beaf","position":"1784455442376501001-297911ff-5395-4fe3-b0d5-1d61294ae2ae"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"81b2ae4ddc50bfa1729ef456eb41c9276df6517259f098a0faf1c04ad9ad66dd","event_uuid":"26f864ae-6008-4439-bf54-1a4dfc662929","position":{"commit_sha":"7e8fca0e3bd6aeb92107b7237b7b4e1f8b153122","position":"1784455635554977277-26f864ae-6008-4439-bf54-1a4dfc662929"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416854646129001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"a9c7c021-4086-424b-94e8-143ec030c1a8","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a"},{"link_uuid":"7aa23a06-083d-4604-8e46-0be5950a10f8","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"3275-b164-2e9b-4e66"}],"description":"## What\nAn OPTIONAL, isolated backfill adapter that mines this machine's Claude Code session transcripts to reconstruct the LOCAL env/integration-diagnosis history (and corroborate attempts/replanning/recovery), which no structural signal captures. Output is LLM-classified and clearly labeled low-confidence; the core command does not depend on this adapter.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/adapters/__init__.py`, `src/rebar/metrics/adapters/claude_transcripts.py` ŌĆö new isolated adapter (imported only by the backfill script, never by the core command).\n- `scripts/backfill_transcripts.py` ŌĆö new: targeted extraction (grep error signatures) -> classify -> write labeled snapshots.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_transcript_adapter.py` ŌĆö new.\n\n## Approach\nBecause all development happened on one machine, the transcripts are a near-complete local record of env toil that leaves no structural trace. To keep the harness portable, the adapter is optional and quarantined behind the backfill script ŌĆö a parallel adapter could target another harness. It is a targeted pass: an **error-signature grep** over the transcript JSONL (patterns such as `LLMUnavailableError`, `ConnectionError`/`connection refused`, `ModuleNotFoundError`, `command not found`, `No such file`, HTTP `429`, `timed out`) selects candidate lines, then a **deterministic keyword/regex classifier** (NOT an LLM ŌĆö so the adapter and its test are self-contained and reproducible, with no model call or human-calibration gate) maps each signature to the classification enum. Every emitted value carries `source=backfill_classified, confidence=classified` ŌĆö that label IS the honest low-confidence signal, and it segregates these values from authoritative structural series. The classification enum (`env_setup`, `dependency`, `integration`, `tooling`, `none`) and the JSON output schema are defined in the adapter module.\n\n**Normative patternŌåÆenum routing table** (first match wins; case-insensitive substring/regex over the transcript line):\n- `env_setup` ŌåÉ `ModuleNotFoundError`, `ImportError`, `No such file or directory`, `virtualenv`/`venv` activation errors, `command not found`.\n- `dependency` ŌåÉ `pip`/`uv` resolution errors, `version conflict`, `Could not find a version`, `incompatible`.\n- `integration` ŌåÉ `ConnectionError`, `connection refused`, `timed out`/`ReadTimeout`, HTTP `429`/`5xx`, `LLMUnavailableError`.\n- `tooling` ŌåÉ `git` errors, `ruff`/`mypy`/`pytest` invocation failures, `Permission denied`.\n- `none` ŌåÉ a candidate line matching no rule above (dropped, not emitted).\n\n**Emitted record JSON schema** (one per classified interval): `{\"kind\": <one of the enum values>, \"signature\": <the matched pattern/string>, \"ts\": <ISO-8601 of the transcript entry>, \"source\": \"backfill_classified\", \"confidence\": \"classified\"}`. The AC assertions (`jq -e`) target `.kind` and `.source`/`.confidence`.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (fixture JSONL transcripts): a transcript with a known env-failure signature is extracted and classified into an `env_setup` interval; a clean transcript yields none; output carries the classified label.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_transcript_adapter.py` passes: a fixture JSONL transcript containing a known env-failure signature (e.g. a `ModuleNotFoundError` line) is extracted and deterministically classified into at least one interval tagged `source=backfill_classified`, `confidence=classified` (`jq -e`); a clean transcript yields 0. No LLM/network call occurs (the classifier is deterministic).\n- [ ] the portability guard holds: a unit test asserts the CORE metrics package does NOT import the adapter ŌĆö specifically that `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` and `src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py` (the modules that exist today) do not import `adapters.claude_transcripts` (assert by scanning each module's source for the adapter import). The `rebar metrics` command's own isolation from adapters is enforced by ticket 9a5a's portability-guard AC ŌĆö this ticket does NOT assert against `_commands/metrics.py` (which 9a5a delivers), to avoid a vacuously-passing scan of a not-yet-existing file.\n- [ ] `scripts/backfill_transcripts.py` is exercised: a test invokes its entry point over a fixture transcript dir and asserts it emits the labeled classified records (so the script ŌĆö not just the adapter ŌĆö is covered).\n- [ ] the classification enum (`env_setup`, `dependency`, `integration`, `tooling`, `none`) and output schema are defined in the adapter module ŌĆö test asserts the enum has exactly these values.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/adapters/claude_transcripts.py","reason":"isolated adapter"},{"path":"scripts/backfill_transcripts.py","reason":"backfill script"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3275-b164-2e9b-4e66"],["depends_on","c085-6d11-d68d-422a"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"aabe5970-5d27-4c57-9c5f-02cdc618cb75","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_id":"538c-ab02-5ec7-4a34","ticket_type":"task","title":"Local Claude-Code-transcript mining adapter (optional, isolated backfill)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["54865087-fb15-40a7-9615-966db0aea35f","61b910ec-19bb-46f0-a652-cbc2f05152af","a9c7c021-4086-424b-94e8-143ec030c1a8","7aa23a06-083d-4604-8e46-0be5950a10f8","731d3ad6-d1b3-49cc-974d-fa200ccef458","ccb6f289-9c03-4ed1-a07c-dfd1073c3173","f685fddf-3f68-44b2-ad67-408d007cb367","4b376e90-9872-4d13-8bf2-9ac4d5e61643","aabe5970-5d27-4c57-9c5f-02cdc618cb75","297911ff-5395-4fe3-b0d5-1d61294ae2ae","26f864ae-6008-4439-bf54-1a4dfc662929"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784455635554977278,"uuid":"3a541d2c-e6d4-4356-855e-2f0d066d79df"}